reviews.review_text: Good things Come for those Wait The recording shows it's age and is a little garbled. At times it seems that this recording holds nothing more than potential nostalgia for those who were there on that night. Not even "Hard to Handle" is able to rattle off the dust and cobwebs. But toward the end of the show, "Good Lovin' pounds some spikes in the punch bowl and somehow the recording sounds fresh again. But the real treat is the Lovelight at the end. Jerry's guitar playing is high voltage and unique from other Lovelights. Pigpen's voice is strong and Soulful and the band conjurs up that Grateful Dead Magic and rewards those who stayed (or listened) until the very end. T
